<br>
No offense Brutul, but as soon as Kunark came out and warriors began getting right click utility effects on armors that are <i>almost</i> on par with some SK abilities, this argument is kinda null and void.  Part of the reason I stuck with my SK through the friggin 20 percent class penalty (before they changed it) along with my 20 percent penalty as a troll was the fact that I did have more utility than non spell casting counterparts.  BUT warriors seem to forget all of the items that have flooded into the game with past expansions which give them abilities that no warrior should have.  <br>
<br>
As it stand, the only things an SK can do that a warrior absolutely cannot do (if the warrior wants to spend the time to aquire the item) are FD, give a buff to others that increases hate generation, and chain cast a line of spells that numerically generate hate on demand.  Granted, for quite a few of those abilities, a warrior has to prey to the gods of SoEs random number generator, but then...you are a warrior and not some finger twiddler.<br>
<br>
Warriors need some help, maybe a timed ability that adds numerical hate.  Thinking something along the line of 500 hate ever 2 minutes or so.  That would still be lower than the terror line that SKs get, which is purely a hate generating spell, but still enough to help lock down aggro on the pull, while having a fast enough refresh time to be useful in most grouping situations.<br>
