<br>
<br>
Quoted from:  Aaoogaa Soulhunter<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://forums.shadowknight.org/showthread.php?s=&threadid=11313">forums.shadowknight.org/s...adid=11313</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
 <br>
 <br>
Warriors are now realizing they need the assistance of other classes to do their job at its peak. SK pulls mob and gains his Agro. Shaman slows and mob stays on SK. Warrior taunts off SK [using aggro + 1 techniques] and has Agro up the wazzo. Rinse repeat with very little problem. The problem is your pride is hurt because you need someone else to make you more effective. Guess that is why this is a grouping game.<br>
<br>
Rangers/SKs/Pallys can generate a lot of agro quickly to keep the mobs off the casters. It does not take you long to taunt off of them and put yourself even higher on the hate list faster than you could ever do on your own. The game is not broken. Sks are finally close to balanced and warriors just have to learn to play well with others. Your not &quot;Gods&quot; anymore your just another class that has a role to fill and the best way to do it is with team effort. You still have a niche but you no longer have a strangle hold on tanking as Clerics no longer have a strangle hold on healing. Welcome to the new Vision...I sorta like it.<br>
<br>
Aaoogaa Soulhunter<br>
57th Circle Ogre Revenant of Rallos Zek<br>
Xegony<br>
Member Synergy Collective<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
/quote<br>
<br>
Karddon 57 Sk<br>
