<br>
We all know how to play EQ. We all understand aggro transfer. We all understand warriors can tank if the rest of the party cooperates.<br>
<br>
The problem is that there is no reason whatsoever for a knight in an experience group to transfer aggro to a warrior, since if there's a knight in the group already, the warrior is sitting in the graveyard with his lfg flag up while a dps class fills that spot instead. And if a knight and a warrior are side by side and a tank is needed, the knight gets picked first because total aggro control + extra abilities &gt; small edge in mitigation in an experience group where defensive is not needed.<br>
<br>
The paladins haven't been so bad, considering, but the shadow knights are worse. Hate to generalize about a class -- but what a bunch of retards. <p><A href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140750><img border="0" src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/bdiebold5/tugedit.jpg"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dwelfnvhal>DwelfnVhal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/03 5:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1882.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Quote</span><hr size=1> Except as usual karddon you guys don't mention that - since you tank ' very nearly' as well anyway - there is no reason to have the warrior in the group piggybacking off your aggro in the first place.<br>
