<br>
I personally am not trying to be a retard, and to be honest don't really care what the hell they do to my class or yours.  I'll adapt and continue to play within the prescribed bounds.<br>
<br>
We all chose our class at some point (knowing the constraints).  Warriors knew they were playing a vanilla class that would rely heavily upon their weapons.  Sk's knew that we would never fulfill a specific role (as most hybrids knew), and could only hope to be desireable in certain situations.<br>
<br>
The current times are in fact great for Sk's.  After spending years LFG, we are once again desireable.  God forbid the &quot;holy trinity&quot; be modified.<br>
<br>
HOWEVER, I do sympathize with warriors. I hate to have success come at the expense of others.  I agree warriors could be HP modified, or have a better gap of mitigation, or even increase the DPS of dual wield.  However, i still have not heard a proposal that wouldn't once again eliminate the need for pallys or sk in xp groups.  If that's the only solution (nerfing knights), oh well.  I'm not gonna cry about a video game.<br>
<br>
People need to remember that this game will NEVER be fully balanced, and the classes will never be in full harmony.  This game goes in cycles- some more favorable than others.  Think back to when knights were last preferable to warriors.  Either wait it out and suck it up, or change classes.  Everyone that has played this game (except maybe clerics) for any period of time, has gone through a period where their class has been &quot;less than desirable.&quot;  Some of us still enjoyed our characters.<br>
<br>
I have no desire to flame or start a war.  If the nerf bat heads our way again, so be it.  I just don't like being called a retard because you happen to not like my class in comparison to yours (at this time).   <br>
<br>
